The underwriting syndicate expects theFinance Ministry to propose a 0.2 to 0.3 percentage point cutin the coupon of the 10-year government bond to be issued inApril from the five pct March issue, underwriting sources said.    The expected proposal is likely to await passage of aprovisional budget for 1987/88 starting April 1 by the LowerHouse of Parliament on March 30, the sources said.    Issue volume is likely to be 1,200 to 1,400 billion yenagainst 475 billion in March, they said. Projected issue priceis around par against 99.50 for the March bond, they said. REUTER&#3;